HEADWORD: Mossback
<hw>Moss"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A veteran partisan;
one who is so conservative in opinion that he may be likened to a stone
or old tree covered with moss.</def> <mark>[Political Slang,
U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

